{{Infobox organization | name = Australian Institute of Petroleum | bgcolor = <!-- header background color --> | fgcolor = <!-- header text color --> | image = | image_border = | size = <!-- default 200px --> | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = <!-- optional --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | map2 = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = | successor = | formation = 1976 | extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> | type = [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]] | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = petroleum industry | headquarters = Canberra | location = | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | region_served = Australia | membership = | language = <!-- official languages --> | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | leader_title = <!-- position title for the leader of the org --> | leader_name = <!-- name of leader --> | key_people = | main_organ = board of directors | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | affiliations = <!-- if any --> | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = {{url|http://www.aip.com.au}} | remarks = | former name = }} The '''Australian Institute of Petroleum''' (AIP) is a representative body for Australia's [[petroleum industry]]. Its headquarters a located in [[Canberra]] and it was established in 1976. The body is managed by a [[Board of directors|board]] composed of chief executives, senior representatives and an [[Executive Director]].
The organisation aims to support the development of sustainable, internationally competitive petroleum products industry.<ref name="healthaip">{{cite web |url=http://www.health.gov.au/internet/main/publishing.nsf/Content/ohp-nicnas-aip |title=Australian Institute of Petroleum |date=20 March 2012 |publisher=Commonwealth of Australia |accessdate=21 August 2012 }}</ref>
The four core members include [[BP|BP Australia]], [[Caltex Australia Limited|Caltex Australia]], [[Mobil#Mobil Australia|Mobil Australia]] and [[Royal Dutch Shell|Shell Company of Australia]].<ref name="cm">{{cite web |url=http://www.aip.com.au/about/members.htm |title=Current Members |publisher=Australian Institute of Petroleum |accessdate=21 August 2012 }}</ref> Its members own and operate all oil refineries in Australia.
The AIP owns the [[Australian Marine Oil Spill Centre]]. It is a member of the [[Australian Industry Greenhouse Network]]. The AIP produces a weekly fuel report detailing average prices for transport fuels by location.
