{{Infobox power station | name = Cestas Solar Park | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = France | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|44|43|16|N|00|48|39|W|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = France | location = [[Gironde]] | status = | construction_began = | commissioned = 2015 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[Neoen]] | operator = | solar_type = PV | solar_cpv_concentration = | solar_csp_technology = | solar_csp_heliostats = | ps_units_manu_model = | ps_electrical_capacity = 300 [[Megawatt|MW]]<ref>[https://www.cnbc.com/2017/05/25/in-france-one-of-europes-most-powerful-solar-farms-marries-innovation-with-scale.html?view=story]</ref> | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = | extra = }} The '''Cestas Solar Park''' is a 300 [[megawatt]] (MW) [[photovoltaic power station]] in [[Cestas]], [[France]]. Built by [[Neoen]], it opened on December 1, 2015. {{Clear}}
