{{Infobox power station | name = Gryta Power Station | name_official = ''Gryta kraftverk'' | image =Gryta kraftverk.JPG | location_map = Møre og Romsdal | location_map_caption = Location in [[Møre og Romsdal]] county | coordinates = {{coord|63|03|20|N|9|10|39|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | location = [[Rindal]], [[Møre og Romsdal]] | country = Norway | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = {{Start date and age|2009}} | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = Gryta Kraft AS | operator = | psps_upper_res = | psps_upper_res_capacity= | psps_penstocks = | psps_lower_res = | psps_lower_res_capacity= | psps_hydraulic_head = 231&nbsp;m | psps_generators = | psps_pumpgenerators = | psps_pumps = | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_manu_model = | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_electrical_capacity = 1.49 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = 34.5%<!-- 4,500 MWh/year / ( 1.49 MW * 365 days/year * 24h/day) = 0.345 --> | ps_annual_generation = 4.5 | ps_annual_gen_year = | website = | extra = }}
The '''Gryta Hydroelectric Power Station''' ({{lang-no|Gryta kraftverk}}) is a [[hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] [[power station]] in the municipality of [[Rindal]] in [[Møre og Romsdal]] [[Counties of Norway|county]], [[Norway]].<ref>[http://www.aftenbladet.no/nyheter/okonomi/Tre-nye-kraftverk-2145975.html Tre nye kraftverk. 2006. ''Aftenbladet'' (10 July).]</ref><ref name="Konsesjon">[http://www.bygg.no/article/16793 Konsesjon til å bygge Gryta kraftverk. 2006. ''Byggeindustrien'' (10 July).]</ref> It is a [[Run-of-the-river hydroelectricity|run-of-river hydro power station]] utilizing a drop of {{convert|231|m|sp=us}} in a tributary of the [[Surna (Norway)|Surna River]].<ref name="Konsesjon"/> Permission was granted for construction in 2006<ref name="Konsesjon"/><ref name="Lillebo">[http://www.tk.no/nyheter/konsesjon-til-gryta-kraftverk/s/1-113-2188081 Lillebo, Eirik. 2006. Konsesjon til Gryta kraftverk. ''Tidens krav'' (July 10).]</ref> and the plant came into operation in 2009.<ref name="Apning">[http://trollheimsporten.custompublish.com/apning-av-gryta-kraft.4737971-152135.html Åpning av Gryta Kraft. 2009. ''Trollheimsporten'' (8 June).]</ref> It is operated by Gryta Kraft AS.<ref name="Lillebo"/><ref name="Apning"/> It operates at an installed capacity of {{nowrap|1.49 [[Megawatt|MW]]}}, with an average annual production of about 4.5&nbsp;GWh.<ref name="Konsesjon"/>
