'''Kogut–Susskind fermions''' are a lattice version of [[Kähler–Dirac fermion]]s,<ref name="banks">{{cite news|title=Geometric Fermions|author = Banks, T, Dothan, Y and Horn, D|date=30 June 1982|journal=Physics Letters B|volume=117|issue=6}}</ref> which obey a first-order differential equation by taking an alternative{{Clarify|date=August 2010}} square root of the [[Laplacian]] than that used by [[Paul Dirac|Dirac]].<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=The Physics of Quantum Fields|author=Stone, M.|date=2000|publisher=Springer New York|isbn=9780387989099|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4urCSqkOrf4C|page=200|accessdate=2015-04-08}}</ref> They are named after [[John Kogut]] and [[Leonard Susskind]].
