'''Lucy Blake''' is an American [[Conservation movement | conservationist]], President of the Northern Sierra Partnership.<ref>{{cite web|title=Staff & Governing Council|url=http://northernsierrapartnership.org/about-nsp/staff-governing-council/|website=Northern Sierra Partnership|accessdate=5 July 2016}}</ref> She was a 2000 [[MacArthur Fellow]].

She founded the Sierra Business Council and won the [[Pat Brown]] Award.<ref name="California Council for Environmental and Economic Balance">{{cite web|title=Mary Nichols wins the 2013 Pat Brown Award for leadership on cap-and-trade.|url=http://www.cceeb.org/events/pba.html|work=PAT BROWN AWARD|publisher=California Council for Environmental and Economic Balance|accessdate=10 April 2013}}</ref>
Blake works for the [[United States Department of Energy|Department of Energy]] on [[energy]] and [[natural resources]].<ref name="A Council for a Livable World">{{cite web|title=Obama Administration: Key Positions|url=http://livableworld.org/news/obama_key_positions/|work=Obama Administration positions as of December 2010|publisher=A Council for a Livable World|accessdate=10 April 2013}}</ref>

